venue.name: Barry's Bootcamp
venue.header: According to the Foursquare community, this place is a 9.1 out of 10.
venue.explanation: We take into account visits and input from our community. You'll see a number on places based off of ratings and tips written by people like you.

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: 30 minutes of cardio/treadmills and 30 minutes of strength training with free weights, bars, bands, and core strength drills in a dance club-like space.

items.text: I think everyone is gay here. No, I mean everyone.
Not for the weak of ambition!  The classes are doable for a beginner but get ready to WORK.  TIP: Get there early because everyone rushes to be on the treadmill first.  Try Rhonda or Harley!
No class is ever the same: Some days you’ll run for 30 minutes on joint-friendly Woodway treadmills then switch to free weights; other days you’ll alternate every five minutes.
Just took Harley's class... Soo good!! Much better than the last one I had.

tip.text: Find custom-designed treadmills, specialized Bootcamp classes, and a protein shake bar at Barry’s. A recent expansion made it one of the biggest gyms in the neighborhood.

sample.text: So hard, but one of the best workouts I have ever had
Harley's 5:30pm workouts are the business. Even...
... especially with Joey, Keoni, or Noah.
